   <taskbody>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the navigation pane, expand<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Documents</uicontrol>, and then click the required document folder.</cmd>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the documents list page, select the appropriate document, and then click<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">View</uicontrol>.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">Alternatively, double-click theappropriate document in the list.
                </info>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The document is opened onthe<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">VIEWER</uicontrol>page.</info>
         </step>
         <step product="Forge_Viewer" class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">If the document file type is mapped to a viewer that supports 2D and 3D drawings, then to switch the view between 2D and 3D, perform the following steps:</cmd>
            <substeps class="- topic/ol task/substeps ">
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">VIEWER</uicontrol>page, click<image href="../../../Icons/FV-image3.png"
                            class="- topic/image "
                            placement="inline">
                        <alt class="- topic/alt ">Document Browser</alt>
                     </image>on the toolbar.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">The<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Document Browser</uicontrol>dialog box is displayed.
                        </info>
               </substep>
               <substep class="- topic/li task/substep ">
                  <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">In the<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Tree</uicontrol>tab, expand<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Model</uicontrol>and then click the appropriate view.</cmd>
                  <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
                     <note class="- topic/note "> If the document supports only 2D view, then the 3D view option is not available.You can view and examine a 2D or 3D drawing design in detail using the viewer tools.<ph product="Exclude_PG_Content" class="- topic/ph ">For information on using the 2D and 3D viewer tools, refer to<xref href="../Using2D3DTools.dita" class="- topic/xref ">Using 2D and 3D Viewer Tools</xref>.</ph>
                     </note>
                  </info>
               </substep>
            </substeps>
         </step>
      </steps>
